<h3>Education </h3>

<strong> Mekelle University: </strong> Established in 2000, Mekelle University is one of Ethiopia's leading universities. It offers a wide range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs and has been instrumental in producing skilled professionals in various fields such as engineering, medicine, and agriculture.
<br> <strong>Adigrat University: </strong> Another significant institution in Tigray, contributing to the educational landscape and providing opportunities for higher education and research.


<strong>School Expansion: </strong> The Tigray region has seen a substantial increase in the number of schools, improving access to education for children in both urban and rural areas.
<strong>Educational Quality: </strong> Efforts have been made to improve the quality of education through teacher training programs, curriculum development, and the provision of educational materials.
Institutions like the Tigray Agricultural Research Institute have been at the forefront of research aimed at improving agricultural practices and productivity in the region.
<br> <strong>Health Research:  </strong>Tigray has also made contributions to health research, addressing local health issues and contributing to national health policies.
